@startuml
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #fcfcfd
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam arrowColor #0f172a
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #fff7d6
skinparam noteBorderColor #b45309
skinparam noteFontColor #334155
skinparam roundcorner 16
title Activity - tenantmanagercontrolplane/Organization
skinparam activity {
  backgroundColor #f8fafc
  borderColor #0f172a
  fontColor #0f172a
  diamondBackgroundColor #e2e8f0
  diamondBorderColor #1d4ed8
  diamondFontColor #0f172a
  startColor #1d4ed8
  endColor #0f172a
  barColor #1d4ed8
}
start
partition "Observe and Bind" {
:Start from shared flow\nshared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg;
:Read desired Organization spec, tracked\nstatus, and delete intent;
if ("Tracked or explicit OCI identity present?") then (yes)
:Get the current OCI resource via\nGetOrganization;
else (no)
:Resolve an existing OCI resource through\nListOrganizations using filters compartment_id;
:Persist the resolved or created OCI identity\ninto status;
endif
}
if ("Delete requested?") then (yes)
partition "Delete" {
:Delete path is not represented by imported\nprovider facts;
:Confirm deletion via GetOrganization or\nListOrganizations until OCI reaches DELETED,\nNOT_FOUND;
:Allow best-effort completion without finalizer\nretention;
}
stop
else (no)
partition "Lifecycle Classification" {
if ("OCI state in retryable set?") then (yes)
:Request requeue while OCI remains in CREATING,\nUPDATING, DELETING;
stop
endif
if ("OCI state is outside success targets?") then (yes)
:Return an unsuccessful reconcile result until\nOCI reaches ACTIVE;
stop
endif
}
partition "Ready and Drift Handling" {
:Compare live OCI state against the imported\nfield surface;
if ("Force-new or conflicting drift detected?") then (yes)
:Reject drift before OCI mutation for force-new\nfields compartment_id, organization_id;
stop
endif
if ("Supported mutable drift detected?") then (yes)
:Apply UpdateOrganization only for mutable\nfields default_ucm_subscription_id;
else (no)
:Skip the no-op mutation path;
endif
:Run provider helper hooks\nupdate=tfresource.UpdateResource when the\nmatching field-driven path executes;
:Apply explicit follow-up semantics\ncreate=none; update=GetWorkRequest ->\nGetOrganization; delete=none;
:Return success for the ACTIVE success state;
:Project required status and finalizer policy\nnone;
:Requeue on provisioning, updating, terminating;
}
endif
stop
note right
shared diagram:
shared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg
Start from the shared reconcile activity and
specialize provider-backed CRUD, wait, and
status-projection details here.
Controller-local activity diagrams add
list-lookup hints, secret policies, delete
handling, and open formal gaps.
archetype batch: Generated service-manager
controllers specialize the shared reconcile path
with formal runtime ownership.
service: tenantmanagercontrolplane
slug: organization
kind: Organization
archetype: generated-service-manager
status/finalizer: required / none
requeue: provisioning, updating, terminating
provider states: create CREATING; update
UPDATING; delete DELETING
follow-up: create=none; update=GetWorkRequest ->
GetOrganization; delete=none
supported drift: default_ucm_subscription_id
reject before mutate: force-new fields
compartment_id, organization_id
create-only fields: none
list lookup:
oci_tenantmanagercontrolplane_organizations
filters compartment_id
conflicts: none
open gaps: none
The published Organization contract is
bind-existing plus update-only. Reconcile binds
by explicit organizationId or a unique
ListOrganizations match on compartmentId, and it
never invents a create path.
Update only reconciles defaultUcmSubscriptionId
and resumes through GetWorkRequest until a
follow-up GetOrganization read confirms the
bound organization state.
Delete is CR-local unbind only. The controller
clears the finalizer immediately, never calls
OCI delete helpers, and treats observed DELETING
or DELETED organization lifecycle as terminating
read state rather than managed delete progress.
FAILED remains terminal non-success and no
Kubernetes secret side effects are part of this
rollout.
end note
@enduml
